statement.p:
Simplify the rational expression.  
\frac{2x+6}{x^{2}-2x-15}
Answer:

Simplify the rational expression
\frac{12 a b^{4}}{21 b^{6}}
in the form \frac{A}{B}.

Perform the indicated operation.  Note that the denominators
are the same.  Simplify the result, if possible.
\frac{y^{2}}{y^{2}-25} + \frac{25-10y}{y^{2}-25}

solution.p:
The denominators are equal.  Add the numerators. Factor and reduce.
\begin{aligned}
\frac{y^{2}}{y^{2}-25} + \frac{25-10y}{y^{2}-25}  \amp  = \frac{y^2 + 25 - 10 y}{y^2 - 25} \amp  \\
                \amp  = \frac{y^2 - 10 y + 25}{y^2 - 25}  \amp  \\
                \amp  = \frac{(y - 5)(y - 5)}{(y + 5)(y - 5)} \amp  \mbox{Reduce common factors}\\
                \amp  = \frac{y-5}{y+5}
\end{aligned}

